    "description": "Anami was an ancient settlement in Egypt. It is marked on the Peutinger map along the route leading from Panopolis to Chenoboskeion. Anami was not included in the Barrington Atlas. It should be noted that compilers of the Tabula Peutingeriana database at the Katholische Universität Eichstätt-Ingolstadt correlate Anami with a place named Antaiopolis/Tkoou (BAtlas 77 FC) that is a standalone place in the Pleiades gazetteer.",
